, <i>Prestage</i>, etc., parallel the local pronunciation of the Lancashire name. Compare   Preston  ."]}]},{"name":"Simon","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Usual English form of   Simeon  , borne in the New Testament by various characters: two apostles, a brother of Jesus, a Pharisee, a leper, a tanner, a sorcerer (who offered money for the gifts of the Holy Ghost, giving rise to the term <i>simony</i>), and the man who carried Jesus's cross to the Crucifixion."],"variants":[{"name":"Simen","meanings":["Usual English form of   Simeon  , borne in the New Testament by various characters: two apostles, a brother of Jesus, a Pharisee, a leper, a tanner, a sorcerer (who offered money for the gifts of the Holy Ghost, giving rise to the term <i>simony</i>), and the man who carried Jesus's cross to the Crucifixion."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs Simon Preston was born about 1344, in Craigmillar, Midlothian, Scotland, United Kingdom. She had at least 4 sons with Sir Simon Preston II. She died about 1400, in Scotland, United Kingdom, at the age of 58."},"et":{"about 1344–about 1400":"umbes 1344–umbes 1400","1340–1400":"1340–1400","1366–1424":"1366–1424","1368–1433":"1368–1433","1370–1424":"1370–1424","1372–1409":"1372–1409","1344–1400":"1344–1400","1340":"1340","1372":"1372","1370":"1370","1424":"1424","1368":"1368","1433":"1433","1400":"1400","1344":"1344","1366":"1366","about 1400":"umbes 1400","about 1344":"umbes 1344","about 1366":"umbes 1366","1409":"1409","Craigmillar, Midlothian, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Craigmillar, Midlothian, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Edinburgh, Midlothian, Scotland":"Edinburgh, Scotland","Scotland, United Kingdom":"Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Craigmillar, Midlothian, Scotland":"Craigmillar, Midlothian, Scotland","Preston Patrick, Westmoreland, England":"Preston Patrick, Westmorland, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Craigmiller Castle, Midlothian, Scotland":"Craigmiller C